    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a potent offensive outlook, anchored by the elite tier production of **Yordan Alvarez** (82.33) and **Kyle Schwarber** (77.03). Both sluggers benefit from favorable wind conditions and strong spot-start opportunities against their respective right-handed matchups. **Trea Turner** (75.86) remains a primary catalyst today; while facing a skilled arm in Shota Imanaga, **Turner**\u2019s dual-threat ability to steal bases\u2014despite the negative hold pressure from the opposing catcher\u2014makes him a high-floor start. We are closely monitoring the lineup postings for **Gary Sanchez**, **Kazuma Okamoto**, **Chase Meidroth**, **Kyle Schwarber**, and **Yordan Alvarez**, as their projected order spots are driving significant efficiency gains in our daily model.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved the marginal outfield corps, where **Hyeseong Kim** (57.15) was retained despite a 35% rain risk and a daunting catcher matchup. He narrowly edged out **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (42.58), whose efficiency was significantly hampered by a negative platoon split against the southpaw Luzardo and a lack of optimized lineup placement. **Josh Smith** (48.28) and **Carson Benge** (49.00) hover near our floor, yet they maintain their spots due to projected platoon advantages. While we are currently carrying **Christian Yelich** on the IL, the rest of the active roster must maintain high efficiency to preserve our seasonal game caps. We are proceeding with caution regarding **Hyeseong Kim**; should the rain risk materialize into a postponement, we will look to rotate in depth from our bench options to ensure we aren't burning a cap on a non-starter.",
